OL,6,FThe council responded to some of the
OL,7,Fallegations made by the GMB union by
OL,8,Fsaying it has "always been clear that
OL,9,Fthe independent investigation report
OL,10,Fwould be considered by the Director of
OL,11,FPlace and Communities in reaching his
OL,12,Fdecision on whether the grounds of the
OL,13,Fgrievance are upheld, and this
OL,14,Freflected the applicable council
OL,15,Fpolicies. That report was considered,
OL,16,Fand the outcome of the Director's
OL,17,Freport was shared with Trade Unions
OL,18,Fand each of the individuals involved
OL,19,Fin the grievance in January 2024."
